jdnjjfgnjdfjgheouihr9ey8940dn

HAPPY BIRTHDAY AMANDA!!!


Yea...she loves the Vote For Pedro wristband I got her. I know it lol. I got her a Happy Bunny wallet too. It's pretty cute.


HAPPY BIRTHDAY AGAIN AMANDA!!!

The breakfast was pretty nice. I should have gotten the pancakes though instead of the french toast. Egh. Didn't taste great. But it was okay. Now I'm making myself hungry. Probably you too. But I have lunch next period. So HAHA :P

Yea...I got to wear my pink J.Lo skirt. It's so cute lol. Joe said I look like a preppy cheerleader. Bad. But...w/e. This entry might be short because I really have nothing to say. I have a test on social studies after lunch, and after that my English test. Ugh. I'm probably going to fail both lol. Here is something fun:

1. Go to your lj calander.
2. Find your 15th entry.
3. Copy and paste the 5th sentence (if you do not have 5 sentences take the 4th one, etc.)
4. Put this in your lj along with the sentence and date of the entry.

December 20th (also during computer class...like right now).

Two bridges held all the weights we had.

Today...was Valentine's day. The stupidest day of the year. Why would you have a holiday to show your love for someone. Aren't you supposed to do that everyday of your life? 

Anyways, tomorrow will be Anti-Valentine's day. My own holiday. Today I wore blue. So tomorrow I will dress in all pink and red. Will be kind of akward, since I usually don't wear ALL pink and red. And...it will be the day after Valentine's day. HAHA. I'm such a dork. Hmph.

Nothing is really happening in school...and that's bad because that means there is nothing to talk about in my rad lj. I think Nikki is abandoning her lj though. It seems she's posting more, and more interesting posts too, in a Xanga. Traitor.

I can't wait to get on the freaking saws already in technology class. I'm tired of these stupid car sketches *throws on the floor and makes a fit*. My co2 car is probably going to lose. I am putting absolutley no effort into this project. I will love you forever if you could sketch a very aerodynamic and winning dragster (co2 car) for me :D.

Anyways, tomorrow is breakfast for champions. Joy. But hey, free breakfast.

You know this lay looks effin awesome.

Thanks Michelle from VortexMB for making the code for me.

This kid had a seisure (sp?) in my last period class. =O . It was so scary. It lasted like 5-10 seconds but like two people thought he faked it? I doubt it. He just fell back onto this girl and she was saying get off me and he then fell on the floor and was shaking and stuff. I thought it was Jason at first because the kid was in a gray sweatshirt and Jason often wears gray sweatshirts. So I thought Jason was making some kind of joke or something. "It's like the week of hell or something"-Jason. lol. *sigh* I hope he's okay now.

Enough about that. It's making me sad.

My mom is going to take me shopping this weekend (again!). I wanna go get converse shoes or something. Pink ones. To match my uhh...3 new skirts? lol. 

Uhhh that's all. Ta Ta children.

Joe (Ali's boyfriend) picked a fight with Jason right after 7th period. I got fucking scared because I was right behind Jason and Joe popped out of no where and started punching Jason. So yea, I sorta had a front row view of the fight? Jason was slammed right into the lockers. I don't think he even tried to hit him back =\. Then they got broken up. 

So then I asked Ali why the hell did he start fighting with him. She kept just laughing and stuff about how that was the best so I don't know if she still wants to be friends with me since I'm a friend of Jason's? But then she answered me and it was something about Jason sexually harrasing her for the past two years????? Joe wasn't even her boyfriend for two years. Then I heard that the whole fight was planned in art (like 6th period or w/e. I don't have it but Ali and Joe do). 

So yea, that's my highlight of the day.

I was supposed to meet with Amanda at the library today after school...but she wasn't in the school library or in the town library. Hmph.

Today...we had a talk. In class...about our 9th grade electives (next school year). Actually...we did most of the listening. The guidance counselor did the talking. I have to have this shizzy filled out by tomorrow >.<

The only really interesting elective on this sheet is Digital Photography (we also get to work with Adobe Photoshop ^.^). So that's definetley going number 1.

For half a year, I'm going to have to take Pool (as in swimming...not billiard games lol). Joy.














I don't know how to swim.

IM GOING TO POLAND WITH MY BEST FRIEND EVER (NIKKI) THIS SUMMER SO HAHA AT YOU BIATCHES LMFAO.

I'm so excited!!!!!!!!!!

 

 

YAY

I'm sitting next to Amanda in study hall. I wish we had Ms.Hearns as our study hall teacher. Yeah...

Anyways....uhhhh

I'm cold. :(

Nothing to write....bye.

December 30, 2004 3:11 PM

She's mean.

Jack is HAWT love

lmao. I just had to put that in. Maybe Amanda will add it to her collection...

Well, yesterday Nikki admitted she was playing a joke on me. I told her she should perform some kind of ritual so the LRA spirits would forgive her for saying that she's NM's best friend LOL. Wow... you can get really screwed for saying that lol. It's probably one of the biggest sin's in the world. Yeah, you know it is. I hope the braindead gang dies.

I have this really awesome picture i wanted to post but unfortunatley I'm in school. Lunch next and I forgot my money again. Actually, I have the money...but in coins. lmao. One time me and Nikki went to Pacsun and I was trying to find enough to buy this roxy wallet [<3]. So I was taking out all these coins and Nikki said I looked like an old grandma buying groceries rofl.

I could go on and on typing but I don't know what about. 

Amanda-thanks for cheering me up.
Jason-which list am I on? lol. Mwahahaha I know everything. And I'm not sod of Antarctica. I'm co-president :-P.
Nikki-That was the most horrible joke on Earth. Right next to the Joey/Nico one lmao. *sigh* So many memories. Why do I feel like I'm writing my testement or something? Egh.

All's good with the world now.

I didn't make the team.

Joy_

Unhappiness_

Both X

http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/6867448/?GT1=6065

Have a moment of silence. Please?

Today was the second tryout day for the basketball team. I think I did better then yesterday. Yeah...i hope i make it :).

I need to find out what the hell Operation Topi is... trust me, you won't know.

My day started with ANOTHER test of my hearing at the nurses office. This time "my hearing was better". Pshh always was good and always will :-P lol.

I was so happy today because I got good scores on my midterms. 99% in science (highest in all of my teachers classes), 87% in math  , 94% in social studies, and 97% in spanish. So I was pretty happy with myself. But then I realized I forgot to bring In my yearbook money. It was due today, but you could bring it in later. Except if you brought the money in by today you would have a few extras in your yearbook and you pay $5 dollars less(I know what you are thinking, big whoop lol). But as the worrywart I am, I got so mad and worried at myself. And the teacher who was in charge of the yearbooks was so mean! She wouldn't even let me leave a deposit with my name  All she said is that I need it by 1:30 PM, and it was almost 1. So I had to call my mom who wasn't home anyway, and she said for me to ask a teacher. psh. Wouldn't it look weird, a teacher giving me $30? But I asked my math/homeroom teacher, and she lent me it. So I had it handed in on time. You all probably think it's not a big deal, but don't you want your name imprinted in gold foil on the cover?? I do! lol  Right after I got this huge headache. And I still have it. *sigh* I lose my sense sometimes... lol

Well, my day started off waiting for the bus for..hmm...15 min? IN THE FREEZING COLD!!!!!!!!!! It was like 12 degrees F !!!! I don't know. We had a different bus and a different bus driver so I guess it's our regular bus drivers fault lol. I always wait on my porch for the bus, and when I finally saw the bus (almost 8 am, homeroom starts at 8:07) I walked to the stop and I couldn't feel my legs! lol.

But besides that, the science and social studies midterms were easy. I just hope math and spanish it too.

Wish me luck!

OMFG MY LAPTOP *PROBABLY* GOT A VIRUS AND IT STOPPED WORKING!

But now it is. We restored it. I lost all my pictures and stuff. But I'm over it. Now.


I seem to have had a pretty bad lucked week. ESPECIALLY.... FRIDAY THE 14TH!!! OOOOOOO
Friday the 13th is my good luck day.

I'm sick too. And I have midterms this week. But I get to go home right after them (11:30, 11:30, 10:00 AM are the times I will be home lol).

Well that's all. Bye.

I saw the movie on abc family yesterday. "She Gets What She Wants". It was funny. XD

Tomorrow. Is. The. Dreaded. ELA. State. Exam. BRING IT ON BIOTCH! lol

In spanish, we get this fake money, "pesetas", for good grades and participation. We can later use those to add points to our test, or get an exempt from a quiz. I'm planning to donate some of mine for a very generous cause. 12,500 for _ _ _ _ so he can get an exempt from the next quiz. He seriously needs it *rolls eyes*. Being nice to people makes me feel all gooey inside. =D . But being evil does too.

Today in phys ed, we had our volleyball championships/finals. My team was playing for first place. AND WE WON. Yeah baby!

And that's all. Bye. 

=(

"If you don't like your job, you don't complain. You go to work and just do it real half-assed. That's the American way!"

We were studying about the working conditions in the late 1800's  and early 1900's in the U.S. So we learned that a lot of people were complaining about the working conditions. Then I remembered that quote and wrote it down on the back cover of my social studies notebook (me, Amanda, and Ali have this little convo thing going on that cover).

I was passing it back and forth with Amanda and once the teacher told us to do out group assignment and everyone started talking she came to our group and picked up the notebook. LMAO. She looked so funny because nothing bad was written there except the word "assed". It was all just funny convo's. So after glancing at it she put it down and told us to pay attention a little more. One legged bitch. I'm multi tasked!lol. Seriously...I was paying attention.

Well, that's the highlight of my day. Talk to all you fellas later.

I applied for that community that Jack posted in one of his entries.

I got banned. She didn't have to be mean. I read the rules I really did. MY APPLICATION FOR SOME REASON CAME OUT MESSED UP AND THATS WHY SHE BANNED ME. GAHHHHH!!!!!!! GRRRRRRRR 
Sorry. I had to let my anger out.

Amanda told us an interesting story today. Her brother saw our science teacher with some gay asian dude in a chinese restauarant. Then Bridget said she saw him with the same guy in this big supermarket... King Kullen. It's a stupid name. Now we are wondering if he's gay.

In Tech, Mr.Pupke took advantage of our big class and made us sand out the writings on the desks. With sandpaper. It smelled like fish. I don't think he ever heard of cleaners such as Pinesol. No, I doubt it. Then in Social Studies Amanda started this convo on the back of my notebook, and out came my new years resolution. Fill the cover up by June.

I have a Spanish quiz tomorrow. And Friday. Ew. Then next week is the ELA 8th grade test. Our english teacher killed us preparing for it. The week after that are midterms. Bleah. But we only have to go to school in the morning for 2-3 days to take a midterm or two each day and then we get to go home. YaY.

This might give a laugh: I went to CVS, and in the parking lot I saw a car with this liscense plate: "OH MR B".

Hahahahahaha. Laugh. Dammit. :-(

One hour until 2005. Wow. Goodbye 2004. I hope 2005 doesn't suck. Hopefully...good times ahead.





HAPPY NEW YEAR

My mom forced me to go to the deli + bank with my dad this morning. I took my cd player and listened to it for that whole 30-40 min. When we were on line in the deli, there were these boxes of chocolates like...to the left of the line. This little girl had one of those tiny barbie dolls they give out in mcdonalds with a happy meal. So she started building like... a house for it with the chocolate boxes. Each time the line moved up she had to put the boxes back and start a new one.

I don't know if I will be doing anything tonight. My dad and I usually go to my uncle's "family" new years party, but now my dad says we shouldn't leave mom. What's the difference... she's going to sleep anyway like every single year.

Anyways you crazy bitches, comment! lol. Bye

lovextrasher That's the color I am lol. Here is a convo I had with a girl I really hate. Like...mega hate. She annoys me. She's mean. She's a slut. (nextidol91 is me its a very old screen name) nextidol91: hey gurl! BabyBugz4191: whose dis? nextidol91: u dunt noe? BabyBugz4191: no? nextidol91: guess :-) BabyBugz4191: i g2g so tell me nextidol91: omg u crazy fuckin bitch i hope u die and burn in hell! you fuckin whore i hope u rot cuz u already started. die die die u ugly ass hoe. u fucking peice of shit get a life instead of being a slut and a skanker! die die die die die Auto response from BabyBugz4191: I am away from my computer right now. Haha. I like being evil to my enemies.

It was fun being in Queens again. It was fun seeing Nikki again. On tuesday we spent most of our time in the Bayside Shopping Center. Damn was it cold lol. But then we went to the movies and watched Meet The Fockers. It's hilarious. (Who in the world would name their child Gaylord?).

When we got back home we played some Monopoly, New York City Edition (Hollerz lol). I was beating her but it was like 12 am and we decided to go to sleep. Then she kept talking crap how we should apologise to the Braindead Gang for all the pranks we played on them. I knew she was joking.

In the morning we continued our monopoly game. She beat my ass. :-( In the end she won by like 6,000. We spent the rest of the day playing board games and making prank phone calls! LOL. Her mom was going to drive us somewhere but she wasn't feeling well :-(.

And you know what? Bryant (sweet-serenity.org/thick-skin) is renovating my other site for me! Yay. He's such a sweetie.

By the way... you better add Nikki to your friends list. suicidenotes14

Egh it's so boring. There is nothing to do.

I would go out in the snow...but it's a tiny bit too cold for me lol. My dog loves it though.

I'm going over Nikki's tomorrow. Yay.

My parents found the guy who knocked out my mom's mirror with his car. He lied and said it wasn't him. It was. The evidence was all there. Bastard.

 

 

Anybody have a baseball bat? I have a certain house to visit.

Hey hey hey!

Christmas was nice. Yes, yes it was. But then there's my brother. "It's not that I want to kill him...it's just...I don't want him to be alive...anymore." He got a stereo system. Bitch.

I don't think there is much else to say, except that Ima be going over Nikki's this week. Yay. =D

Tata.

Some dude in Copiague knocked out my mom's car mirror and made it a hit and run. My mom was working a lot the past weeks and she was going to buy me something for Christmas. Now she can't. She's not even going to be home tomorrow or Saturday until night. She would have gone but the police came to our house to file a report and that took f o r e v e r.

I know I seem kind of selfish or stubborn and that I should be thankful for what I've got but there's nothing in my life that seems to go right. So what the hell am I supposed to be thankful for? The family that's never there for me?


I'm disgusted at myself. Bye.

We played pictionary in Spanish because only 9 people were in. We did a battle of the sexes, boys against girls. Girls won. Why? Because we rock.


In social studies Amanda got obssessed over a green crayola crayon.


Damn You All!

I'm in school. Again. I think this is the only time I update my journal?

Anyways, yesterday I overslept and missed the bus, and since everybody in my house leaves before me, I was left to stay home. And do nothing. Actually I watched reruns of "The Real Gilligans Island". I spent the rest of my day watching reruns of "Family Guy"

I just had a math test, it was pretty easy actually. Maybe I will get a 100.

I need to go over Amanda's house sometime. She has the Napolean Dynamite movie. I need to watch it bad.





Out, and about.

I'm in school yet again.

In computers right now, last period I was in Tech.








Our bridge held 70lbs. Only.



Two bridges held all the weights we had. 505lbs. One of them broke. The other didn't. The one that did break was more efficient.







Out of ten groups, we came in 9th place.



We suck.

Well, Nikki came over yesterday. She got me a Webcam, lotion/body wash pack that smells really good, a book, and lip gloss. All for my birthday and Christmas. She is so nice.

We stayed up until like 2 am because we were bored. And then the flashlight was freaking us out so we got scared. We thought the devil was in my room lol.

And then this morning we were playing with a hacky sack.

And then... her mom picked her up. LOL. So pretty much the rest of the day I was playing with the webcam. =\



I don't wanna go to school tomorrow.

...TO ME!

Yes children it's my birthday lol. I got a digital camera from my mom and dad. :-) I love it. 

I didn't get to crush mine, Amanda's, and Jason's bridge in Tech today. We have to wait until Monday. Sucks.

Ummm... i got some other presents. =\. Nikki might come over tomorrow so it will be cool because we are going to rock this damn town again.

This is for you Amanda, even though you probably are reading this because I told you to.

http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v398/evilmunchkin/DSCN0053.jpg
http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v398/evilmunchkin/DSCN0054.jpg

you will probably like the second one better, but in the first one you can see my hair, and the second one half of my finger rofl.

ttyl children

I'm sitting in study hall again.

It's sooooo boring *pokes avatar*

Tomorrow is my birthday :-)

I'm in study hall with Amanda. We can't get the Coheed to play. Some kids listening to crappy music. But my apple candy tastes good.



Amanda says "Hello mother truckers."





Tata.





Goddamn laptop.

I haven't blogged in a while. Sorry.

Today wasn't very interesting. In study hall everyone just grabbed a laptop and played games or listened to music. Me and Amanda listened to Coheed and Cambria, but then it stopped playing :-O *gasp*.

The day just dragged on and was pretty boring. Jason acted freaky on the bus. =\. 

I'm considering tutoring _ _ _ _ in spanish so I could spend more time with him =D.

Anywayz, tomorrow I'm going birthday/christmas shopping. Yea kinda late...but who cares. L8er.

I was making a mix cd yesterday, and I was really stupid because I finalized the cd without checking the songs.

Turns out on one of the songs, for about 3 seconds, 3 times through out the song, some ghost voice comes on and says "Take the ecstasy. Take it" =|

Amanda told us her wonderful story of using a saw to try to fix a necklace, ending up making a deep cut in her finger.

Children...it's not safe to play with sharp tools. =D

Life is shitty right now.

People are mad at me. I'm mad at people. I'm depressed.

Are apologies accepted in this world?

The world is full of dipshits.

I think I'm going to start a protest to demolish this damn school. I don't know about everybody else, but I'm going to move back to Queens.

I love volleyball, but in Gym, it sucks. There is like 10 people on a team, and these guys on my team keep moving from their positions just to get the ball. EXCUSE ME BUT I CAN GET IT TOO!!!!. lol. I admit, my serve came out bad. But still, I had the perfect chance to hit the ball. And I did. Right after some fatso kid slammed into me and almost pushed me down. Bitch.

I walked home after school with Jason and Amanda. When we got to this big supermarket, we put Jason in a shopping cart and pushed him to the other end of the parking lot.

I want that pink fluffy pocketbook from Industrial.

Kathy is sad

Kathy is sad because we did not win 1,000 dollars in a Daily News game.

Kathy is happy.

Kathy is happy because she will get a pink fluffy pocketbook for her birthday which is 15 days away.

So today we went on our social studies trip to Teddy Roosevelt's house at Oyster Bay. That house was HUGE, and during his time, he had it built for only $17,000???? :-(

Ofcourse, we kept daring Amanda to lick a wall lmao, then this banister. And she didn't want to so I wiped the banister, and told her it's all clean now Amanda, you won't get AIDS or HIV lmao.

Outside and on the bus we created a Mosh Pit. :-D On our way back on the bus we waved to people in cars. squished our faces on the window, Amanda licked our shoes LMAO. The bottoms of our shoes. Can you believe it? She's got guts! And after doing that she drank some of Scott's milkshake from McDonalds, and had me drink some of it after her. *yuck* LOL. Well, now we are all one big happy family.

Ofcourse, there are all those other moments where we all just cracked up laughing.

Today was kind of boring, but in most of my classes, half the kids were gone on a field trip so we didn't get a lot of work. In Tech, Jason got thrown out of class because he was laughing, so until he came back, me and Amanda actually got some work done on our bridge drawing. In social studies, my group is already done with our project, so me and Bridget just went on the computer.

Afterschool I walked home with Jason and Amanda, and it was pretty far for me and Jason. And of course, right when we left the school I need to go pee. When I got home I barged into the bathroom. :-) And that was my wonderful day. Goodbye.

FRIDAY WAS THE SHIZ. Nikki came over and it was the craziest day ever. We went out for a walk around the block with my dog, and when we were walking down back my street again, I started telling Nikki a story and got distracted. Suddenly she yells at me to get out of the way and there is this car stopped right in front of me and I jump out of the way with my dog. The guy in the car (guy=SMOKIN hot) was laughing his head off. Then later when we went for pizza, we ate at the pizzeria and then got some ice cream(i got a strawberry shortcake). And we were walking home and this group of *slightly* hot guys walk past us and one of them says to me "Can I have a piece of that strawberry shortcake?". LOL. We just walked on.

Then when we went walking around again Nikki found tape from a video cassette and she started dragging it a long with her. rofl. It was the funniest thing ever. And it started getting dark out and we walked past this house where a group of kids where playing in the front yard, and they started cursing at us and stalking us. So when we walked past their house again they called their DAD over and told on us. So damn straight I straightened it out with him. :-P

That was an awesome day. Today was an OK-AY day. Funniest thing was in English when our teacher was asking for an example where we can get a literal defenition and a figurative defention, so I said "I get so much homework I could die doing it". And Jason said the it's true, we could die from homework, because if you don't have blood clots and you get a paper cut, you can bleed to death. Then in Spanish we played with telephones.
Okay so for some reason i decided to create a livejournal. Aren't i cool.
